
command to host local server:
python3 -m http.server

u access file:/// from a http:// protocol using: 
localhost:8000

that mean that for example if want to access a file called: '<PATH>/[<DIRECTORY>/]<FILENAME>.html'
you do this command from terminal:                           cd <PATH>
then u launch the host local server command:                 python3 -m http.server

to open 'index.html' u just do:                              http://localhost:8000
to open [<DIRECTORY>/]<FILENAME>.html u do this:
and then u write on the browser this:                        http://localhost:8000/[<DIRECTORY>/]<FILENAME>.html

